-- Kazakhstan Gold Reserves Rose 1.7% in December, IMF Data Show
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2013-01-27T18:44:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-27/kazakhstan-gold-reserves-rose-1-7-in-december-imf-data-show.html
Kazakhstan gold reserves rose 1.7
percent in December to 3.707 million ounces, according to data
on the International Monetary Fund website.  Philippines gold reserves fell 1 percent in November from
October while  Mexico ’s holdings were down 0.1 percent in
December to 4.004 million ounces, according to the IMF. Russia’s
gold reserves climbed 2.1 percent to 30.793 million ounces,
according to the data.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  